FBIS3-10882 "drlat050_a_94006" FBIS-LAT-94-050 Document Type:Daily Report 15 Mar 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Raul Castro Greets Ciego de Avila EJT Brigade FL1503020894 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in Spanish 0100 GMT 15 Mar 94 FL1503020894 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] In Ciego de Avila, the first Youth Labor Army [EJT] brigade to cut 1 million arrobas of sugarcane in Cuba has received a letter of congratulations from Army General Raul Castro. The average age of the brigade members is barely 18 years. However, they have been capable of the labor feat of cutting 1 million arrobas in slightly less than 60 workdays. This result places them at the head of the EJT forces participating in the sugarcane harvest and is a repeat of last year's success. [passage omitted] They have once again raised high their battalion flag -- the 531st -- of the Batalla del Ubero Camp in Venezuela Municipality. The brigade members were happy to receive the letter of congratulations from Army Gen. Raul Castro for being an outstanding unit. [passage omitted]
